Interface IStructureConst

    • getAnimationRange

      Rectangle getAnimationRange()
      Gets the rectangle describing the limits within an animation of this door takes place.

      At no point during an animation will any animated block leave this cuboid, though not guarantees are given regarding how tight the cuboid fits around the animated blocks.

      Returns:
      The animation range.

    • isOwner

      boolean isOwner(UUID player)
      Checks if a player with a given UUID is a (co-)owner of this structure with any level of ownership.

      If the level of ownership matters, use getOwner(UUID) instead.

      Parameters:
      player - The UUID of a player.
      Returns:
      True if the player with the given UUID is an owner of this structure with any level of ownership.

    • isOwner

    • getOpenDir

      MovementDirection getOpenDir()
      Gets the MovementDirection this IStructure will open if currently closed.

      Note that if it's currently in the open status, it is supposed go in the opposite direction, as the closing direction is the opposite of the opening direction. This isn't taken into account by this method.

      Returns:
      The MovementDirection this IStructure will open in.

    • getBlockCount

      default int getBlockCount()
      Retrieve the total number of blocks this IStructure is made out of. If invalidated or not calculated * yet, it is (re)calculated first.

      It's calculated once and then stored until invalidated.

      Returns:
      Total number of blocks this IStructure is made out of.

    • getDimensions

      default Vector3Di getDimensions()
      Gets the dimensions of this structure.

      If a structure has a min and max X value of 120, for example, it would have an X-dimension of 0. If the min X value is 119 instead, it would have an X-dimension of 1.

      Returns:
      The dimensions of this structure.
